  "text": "Although mammography has been successful in screening high-risk breast cancer patients, about 20% of cases remain undetected by this technology. It is hoped that metabolomic profiling combined with other detection technologies may improve the sensitivity and specificity of cancer detection and diagnosis. Toward this end, the role of chemokine receptor CXCR4 in breast cancer aggressiveness was demonstrated by Vermeer et al. [CITATION_1] .",
